<div id="review_369844904" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/369844904" />
    <a title="Stacey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/399175-stacey"><img alt="Stacey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464114155p2/399175.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/369844904?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stacey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stacey" href="/user/show/399175-stacey">Stacey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer369844904" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1585652277747794799">When my 10 year old says, &quot;Mom, you HAVE to read this!&quot; and checks my progress, it melts my heart. I&apos;m only a few pages in, but I&apos;m wondering why my 5th grade teacher didn&apos;t offer great books(or any for that matter) for us to read!<br/><br/>This truly is YA. It&apos;s full of adolescent antics, lights up the importance of family and told the story of an incident that happened in Birmingham &apos;63. It&apos;s an important read for kids and provided the opportunity to talk about the Civil Rights Movement.<br/><br/>My favorite part</span>
  <span id="freeText1585652277747794799" style="display:none">When my 10 year old says, "Mom, you HAVE to read this!" and checks my progress, it melts my heart. I'm only a few pages in, but I'm wondering why my 5th grade teacher didn't offer great books(or any for that matter) for us to read!<br /><br />This truly is YA. It's full of adolescent antics, lights up the importance of family and told the story of an incident that happened in Birmingham '63. It's an important read for kids and provided the opportunity to talk about the Civil Rights Movement.<br /><br />My favorite part of the book was when my son read to me his favorite chapter while I ate dinner. Priceless. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1585652277747794799" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

