        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1109450373" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9260965001641646067"><i> The Watsons Go to Birmingham-1963 </i> is a great historical fiction book to read the author of this book is Christopher Paul Curtis. The book shows you what it was like to be in an African American family in 1963 of the southern and northern parts of America. I for one loved <i> The Watsons Go to Birmingham-1963<i></i> I thought it was really funny at some parts but really sad at other parts. I don&apos;t have a brother and I got to see what it was like having an older brother. My favorite part of the book was d</i></span>
  <span id="freeText9260965001641646067" style="display:none"><i> The Watsons Go to Birmingham-1963 </i> is a great historical fiction book to read the author of this book is Christopher Paul Curtis. The book shows you what it was like to be in an African American family in 1963 of the southern and northern parts of America. I for one loved <i> The Watsons Go to Birmingham-1963<i></i> I thought it was really funny at some parts but really sad at other parts. I don't have a brother and I got to see what it was like having an older brother. My favorite part of the book was during the bombing. It was horribly frightening, but that part kept me on the edge of my seat more than any book I have ever read. The book was great although I really wish the epilogue told us what happened 5-10 years later. I'd definitely recommend this book. </i></span>
  <a data-text-id="9260965001641646067" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
