<span id="freeTextContainer13216155162241429896">Reread. This book, a consistent favorite in my classroom over the years, is wildly popular with my current students. We meet the Weird Watsons and through them, experience the Civil Rights Movement and its impact on individual children and their families. <br/><br/>The Watsons Go to Birmingham also launched Christopher Paul Curtis&apos; writing career, an immeasurable gift to all of us who read his work. </span>
  <span id="freeText13216155162241429896" style="display:none">Reread. This book, a consistent favorite in my classroom over the years, is wildly popular with my current students. We meet the Weird Watsons and through them, experience the Civil Rights Movement and its impact on individual children and their families. <br /><br />The Watsons Go to Birmingham also launched Christopher Paul Curtis' writing career, an immeasurable gift to all of us who read his work. </span>
